"Riobó P., Paz B., Franco J.M., Vázquez J.A., Murado M.A.","Proposal for a simple and sensitive haemolytic assay for palytoxin. Toxicological dynamics, kinetics, ouabain inhibition and thermal stability",2008,"Harmful Algae","7","4",,"415","429",,,10.1016/j.hal.2007.09.001,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-43049109137&partnerID=40&md5=6041e80a4658af9dd0b1e9de8674d64f","Grupo de Fitoplancton Tóxico, Instituto Investigacións Mariñas (CSIC), Eduardo Cabello 6, 36208 Vigo, Galicia, Spain; Grupo de Reciclado y Valorización de Residuos, Instituto Investigacións Mariñas (CSIC), Eduardo Cabello 6, 36208 Vigo, Galicia, Spain","Riobó, P., Grupo de Fitoplancton Tóxico, Instituto Investigacións Mariñas (CSIC), Eduardo Cabello 6, 36208 Vigo, Galicia, Spain; Paz, B., Grupo de Fitoplancton Tóxico, Instituto Investigacións Mariñas (CSIC), Eduardo Cabello 6, 36208 Vigo, Galicia, Spain; Franco, J.M., Grupo de Fitoplancton Tóxico, Instituto Investigacións Mariñas (CSIC), Eduardo Cabello 6, 36208 Vigo, Galicia, Spain; Vázquez, J.A., Grupo de Reciclado y Valorización de Residuos, Instituto Investigacións Mariñas (CSIC), Eduardo Cabello 6, 36208 Vigo, Galicia, Spain; Murado, M.A., Grupo de Reciclado y Valorización de Residuos, Instituto Investigacións Mariñas (CSIC), Eduardo Cabello 6, 36208 Vigo, Galicia, Spain","Benthic dinoflagellates of the genus Ostreopsis are important components of subtropical and tropical marine coral reef-lagoonal environments. Currently, as a result of global warming and trade globalization, they are also distributed worldwide. These microalgae are shown to produce palytoxin, one of the most potent non-protein marine toxins known. The haemolytic assay is a very easy, rapid and sensitive method to determine palytoxin. However, under the conditions reported in previous works this assay is inadequate for a rigorous dose-response treatment, since: (1) it produces degenerate sigmoidal profiles, with a pronounced slope which makes the calculation of the ED50 very sensitive to the experimental error; (2) at the usual work temperature, the in vitro stability of the system is low, which accentuates the variability and ambiguity of the response. To resolve these problems haemolysis of sheep erythrocytes is studied, including it's toxicological dynamics, kinetics, inhibition by ouabain and response to temperature. The results show that, to obtain a smoother, more stable and reproducible response, it is necessary to apply two resources simultaneously: operation at a moderate temperature and partial inhibition of the palytoxin by ouabain. It also produces highly reliable parameters and allows strict equivalencies to be established with the mouse bioassays, a traditional reference point, though bioethically questionable and 20 times less sensitive than the bioassay proposed here. © 2007 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.","Haemolytic assay; Kinetics; Ostreopsis; Ouabain; Palytoxin; Toxicological dynamics","Anthozoa; Dinophyceae; Ostreopsis; Ovis aries; Strophanthus gratus",,,,,,"Alcala, A.C., Alcala, L.C., Garth, J.S., Yasumura, D., Yasumoto, T., Human fatality due to ingestion of the crab Demania reynaudii that contained a palytoxin-like toxin (1988) Toxicon, 26, pp. 105-107; Artigas, P., Gadsby, D.C., From the cover: Na+/K+-pump ligands modulate gating of palytoxin-induced ion channels (2003) NAS, 100, pp. 501-505; Bignami, G.S., A rapid and sensitive haemolysis neutralization assay for palytoxin (1993) Toxicon, 31, pp. 817-820; Brzezinska-Slebodzinska, E., Species differences in the susceptibility of erythrocytes exposed to free radicals in vitro (2003) Vet. Res. Commun., 27, pp. 211-217; Canavos, G.C., (1992) Probabilidad y estadística. Aplicaciones y métodos, Vol., , McGraw Hill, Madrid; Fukui, M., Murata, M., Inoue, A., Gawel, M., Yasumoto, T., Ocurrence of palytoxin in the Trigger fish Melichtys vidua (1987) Toxicon, 25, pp. 1121-1124; Granéli, E., Ferreira, C.E.L., Yasumoto, T., Rodrigues, E., Neves, M.H.B., Sea urchins poisoning by the benthic dinoflagellate Ostreopsis ovata on the Brazilian coast (2002) Book of Abstracts of Xth International Conference on Harmful algae, , Florida; Habermann, E., Ahnert-Hilger, G., Chhatwal, G.S., Beress, L., Delayed haemolytic action of palytoxin (1981) Biochem. Biophys. Acta, 649, pp. 481-486; Habermann, E., Chhatwal, G.S., Ouabain inhibits the increase due to Palytoxin of cation permeability of erythrocytes (1982) Naunyn-Schmiedeberg's Arch. Pharmacol., 319, pp. 101-107; Hilgemann, D.W., From a pump to a pore: how palytoxin opens the gates (2003) Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A., 100, pp. 501-505; Holtrop, G., Petrie, J., McElhiney, J., Dennison, N., Can general anaesthesia be used for the paralytic shellfish poison bioassay? (2006) Toxicon, 47, pp. 336-347; Huntley, J.S., Hall, A.C., Aspects of the haemolytic reaction induced by kanagawa hemolysin of Vibrio parahaemolyticus (1994) Toxicon, 32, pp. 1397-1412; Moore, R.E., Scheuer, P.J., Palytoxin: a new marine toxin from a coelenterate (1971) Science, 172, pp. 495-498; Murado, M.A., González, M.P., Vázquez, J.A., Dose response relationships: an overview. A generative model and its application to the verification of descriptive models (2002) Enzyme Microb. Technol., 31, pp. 439-455; Murado, M.A., Vázquez, J.A., The notion of hormesis and the dose-response theory: a unified approach (2007) J. Theor. Biol., 244, pp. 489-499; Onuma, Y., Satake, M., Ukena, T., Roux, J., Chanteau, S., Rasolofonirina, N., Ratsimaloto, N., Yasumoto, T., Identification of putative palytoxin as the cause of clupeotoxism (1999) Toxicon, 37, pp. 55-65; Riobó, P., Vázquez, J.A., Murado, M.A., Cacho, E., Paz, B., Franco, J.M. Mouse bioassay for palytoxin: dose-response and dose-death time relationships, unpublishedShalel, S., Streichman, S., Marmur, A., Modeling surfactant-induced haemolysis by Weibull survival analysis (2002) Colloids Surf. B: Biointerfaces, 27, pp. 223-229; Taniyama, S., Arakawa, O., Terada, M., Ni